lead_paragraph: Three years of war, according to announcements made in Parliament yesterday, cost the British Empire forces 92,089 killed, 226,719 missing, 88,294 wounded and 107,891 taken prisoner, or a total of 514,993. The toll of prisoners was swollen by Indian troops taken at Hong Kong and Singapore.
